{"id":"2209.07560","submitter":"Kexue Zhang","authors":"Kexue Zhang, Elena Braverman, Bahman Gharesifard","title":"Event-Triggered Control for Discrete-Time Delay Systems","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Automatica 147 (2023) 110688","doi":"10.1016/j.automatica.2022.110688","report-no":null,"categories":"math.OC cs.SY eess.SY","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This study focuses on event-triggered control of nonlinear discrete-time\nsystems with time delays. Based on a Lyapunov-Krasovskii type input-to-state\nstability result, we propose a novel event-triggered control algorithm that\nworks as follows. The control inputs are updated only when a certain\nmeasurement error surpasses a dynamical threshold depending on both the system\nstates and the evolution time. Sufficient conditions are established to ensure\nthat the closed-loop system maintains its asymptotic stability. It is shown\nthat the time-dependent portion in the dynamical threshold is essential to\nderive the lower bound of the times between two consecutive control updates. As\na special case of our results, we demonstrate the performance of the designed\nevent-triggering algorithm for a class of linear control systems with time\ndelays. Numerical simulations are provided to demonstrate the effectiveness of\nour algorithm and theoretical results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Sep 2022 18:48:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-16"}
